author: wn.com
title: Dem: Boehner loss blow for state
text: The senior member of Ohio’s U.S. House delegation blames Rep. Jim Jordan for spurring House Speaker John Boehner to retire, a development that she says is unprecedented and will cause “irreparable harm” to the state. Rep. Marcy Kaptur, a Toledo Democrat first elected in 1983, said the Freedom Caucus — a group of 40 or so ultraconservative House members led by Jordan — caused so many headaches for GOP House leaders that a frustrated Boehner announced he was leaving Congress after 24 years.
